
`IShellLink` allows to attach extra *data blocks* to a *Shell link*.
-
There are five types of blocks that are currently supported:
table { ll
   `EXP_DARWIN_LINK` ☰ The link's Windows Installer ID.
   `EXP_SPECIAL_FOLDER` ☰ Special folder information.
   `EXP_SZ_LINK` ☰ The target name.
   `→ Windows/development/Portable-Executable/subsystem/console/NT_CONSOLE_PROPS` ☰ Console properties (font, colors, size, position etc.)
   `NT_FE_CONSOLE_PROPS` ☰ The console's → Windows/development/code-page[code page].
table }


{ Methods

  table { ll

    `AddDataBlock` ☰ Adds a data block to a link.
    `CopyDataBlock` ☰ Retrieves a copy of a link's data block.
    `GetFlags` ☰ Gets the current option settings.
    `RemoveDataBlock` ☰ Removes a data block from a link.
    `SetFlags` ☰ Sets the current option settings.

  table }

}

sa:

  The interface ID of `IShellLinkDataList` is `{45E2B4AE-B1C3-11D0-B92F-00A0C90312E1}`.
 
  → Windows/development/WinAPI/Shell/read-lnk-file
